data.description: A MUST SEE! 2 Bdrm/2Ba/oversized 2-car garage. Single family. No HOA. This home is a rare gem for Holiday. It offers so many little extras you'll wonder how you managed without them before. You'll love the fully remodeled master suite. It has a relaxing deep jetted tub with a separate oversized shower and an organized walk-in closet. Double sink vanity. The outlets have USB charging ports for your devices and each bathing area has its own walled dimmer switch for those moments when you just need a hint of light. Enjoy your bathroom "me-time" with a Bluetooth exhaust fan that connects to your devices. You can play music or whatever you like from your phone or any other Bluetooth compatible device. The fully remodeled eat-in kitchen is equipped with matching stainless steel frig, microwave, dishwasher and stove as well as a built-in wine rack. It also offers an insta-hot built into the sink for those moments when you want hot water fast. Ample pantry space. The living room is spacious and has an abundance of natural light. The home has a split floor plan with ceiling fans throughout. The guest room is located on the opposite side from the master with lots of closet space and floor to ceiling windows. The guest bath has a tub/shower combo. There's an extra open room you can use as a dining area or a game room. The utility room includes a washer and dryer. The back patio is screened and has privacy/hurricane draw downs. It's a great place to sip your morning coffee while listening to the birds serenade you. Attic is accessible via fold down stairs. The home is located on the West side of U.S. Highway 19. Flood insurance required. CALL TODAY to set up a viewing. THIS HOME WON'T LAST LONG.
data.whatILove: I love all the extra little joys that this home offers. In addition, it's a short bike ride to the Gulf where you can see dolphins daily. And during Autumn and Winter, you can witness manatees congregate. Close to wildlife and within minutes of the 3 Anclote parks where you can walk your dog, fish and even go boating. Springfield Dr is peaceful and you can see the lake across the street. It offers a gorgeous sunset view.
